CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 12, 1957, page A15, reads: "Lush Mink made an effective frame for the audaciously lovely Sara Lou Harris when she appeared in Pittsburgh, in a fashion show sponsored by the Pittsburgh National Council of Negro Women, Saturday night."
TitMainTitle: Sara Lou Harris modeling sheath evening dresses, gloves, and mink fur coat at the Pittsburgh National Council of Negro Women fashion show
